    public final class BarcodeReadEvent

    • Method Detail

      • getBarcodeData

        public String getBarcodeData()
        Retrieves the bar code data as a String. If you need the data as bytes, you can call String.getBytes(Charset) on the result of this method. The Charset needed to retrieve the bar code data as bytes can be determined by calling getCharset().
        Returns:
        The bar code data as a String.

      • getCharset

        public Charset getCharset()
        Retrieves the character encoding of the bar code data. This encoding information allows you to get access to the original binary data encoded in the bar code.
        Returns:
        The character encoding of the bar code data
        See Also:
        getBarcodeData()

      • getCodeId

        public String getCodeId()
        Retrieves the unique characters defined by Honeywell to identify symbologies.
        Returns:
        The symbology identifier.

      • getAimId

        public String getAimId()
        Retrieves the AIM identifier of the bar code.
        Returns:
        The AIM ID.

      • getTimestamp

        public String getTimestamp()
        Retrieves the date/time in ISO 8601 format.
        Returns:
        The date/time string.

      • getBarcodeBounds

        public List<Point> getBarcodeBounds()
        Retrieves a list of 4 points representing the polygon that approximates the boundary of the bar code. The first point is the upper left corner of the bar code, then upper right, bottom, right and finally bottom left.
        Returns:
        The list of Point objects representing the barcode bounds.
